{"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"anchor":"Overview","level":2,"text":"Overview","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"TUIkit uses a layered event dispatch system. When a key is pressed, it passes through up to three layers. The first layer that consumes the event wins: remaining layers are skipped.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":null,"code":["Terminal raw bytes","      │","      ▼","  KeyEvent.parse()","      │","      ▼"," ┌─────────────────────────────┐"," │  Layer 1: Status Bar Items  │  Shortcuts with actions (e.g. \"q\" quit)"," └────────────┬────────────────┘","              │ not consumed","              ▼"," ┌─────────────────────────────┐"," │  Layer 2: View Handlers     │  .onKeyPress() modifiers (deepest view first)"," └────────────┬────────────────┘","              │ not consumed","              ▼"," ┌─────────────────────────────┐"," │  Layer 3: Default Bindings  │  q=quit, t=theme, a=appearance"," └─────────────────────────────┘"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Additionally, "},{"code":"Ctrl+C","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" (SIGINT) is handled at the OS signal level "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"before"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":" any of these layers: it always terminates the application."}]},{"anchor":"Available-Keys","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Available Keys"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"code":"Key","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" enum defines all keys that TUIkit can recognize from terminal input:","type":"text"}]},{"anchor":"Character-Keys","level":3,"type":"heading","text":"Character Keys"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Any printable character is represented as "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".character(Character)"},{"type":"text","text":":"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":[".onKeyPress(Key.from(\"x\")) {","    \/\/ handle \"x\" key"